rComments: Best professor every, if you have the time go and have a conversation about anything she is a well rounded amazing professor. Professor Nacol is very understanding and gives amazing advice whether it is course-based or general university information. She is always more than willing to help.

Although the prof was amazing as a person, the overall course had an insane amount of workload. Her and her TA's were never on the same page and the final exam is ridiculously hard. The readings are so lengthy and my advice is to avoid this class as much as possible
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy', 'So many papers']

rComments: Nacol is the best professor you'll ever have if you're lucky to ever have her. Her lectures are disciplined and structured perfectly, extremely substantive, and crystal clear. There is no better professor for political theory you'll ever get.
Shes really sweet and caring about her students. She makes sure to thoroughly cover all materials, which makes it so much easier to understand the most important points. Overall great prof.

rComments: Nacols pretty cool, in 200 she focused on ancient theorists which I hate so there's my bias, however, she explained the readings in lecture so well I didn't even have to read, I recommend readings but her lectures are very informative. She had a good dose of theorists ex, Locke Machiavelli, Hobbes, Aquinas, Plato, Aristotle, Cicero and others.
